I dont want to go to deep into everything that is wrong with children and religion in one sentence, or just how cruel religion can be. If you have something to say about that say it elsewhere because I dont care. This thread is about the summer camps. Thanks for reading 18/18.

As a side note, all of the adults and organisers were part of one big christian community and school. Everyone there had religious affiliations of some sort and of course were preeching bullshit 24/7. I heavily distance myself from these people now as an adult myself 17/

My mom specifically bought those for the KIDS in the camp and she made that very clear to them. When I told her about it she was fucking outraged, herself working with kids as well. She advised me against taking part in one of these camps 16/

Every kid got 2 (two) pieces of the snack and about 1 dl of the juice. When I asked what happens to the rest of the 3 buckets and 12 litres of juice, the camp leader told me it will be distributed between the organisers, because they worked so hard to set up the camp 15/

About 2 years later I was taking part in a christian scout camp. My mom brought the campers a lot of snacks (see pic), about 5KG (5 big buckets) and about 18 (1,5*6*2) litre of fruit juice for the 50 kids residing there. 14/ https://t.co/yYJ9gHgF9s

The food was also trash. Any snacks our parents sent with us to share with our friends were confiscated in the first day of the camp and then probably distributed among the adults. We never saw those snacks again. This is not the only time they did something similar. 13/

Being kids we managed to (somehow) build an entire bunker out of sticks we found and some trees aligning well, to then be prohibited to play there for reasons never explained to us. I guess they just hated fun they couldnt be part of. 12/

Freetime was essentially non-existent. The camp was fully rebuilt with a lot of playground toys and a huge forest with many resources to build a forest bunker. However, because we had to attend pieties (calvinist school) 3-5 times a day they were basically left unused 11/

Also, violance, bullying and other stuff was never a problem unless it occured to the kids with rich or powerful parents. One of the volunteers was the son of the principal, the other was the niece or whatever to some high position pastor. 10/

(sorry i cant spell volunteer wtv) Looking back now I see how irresponsible and laid back they were and had literally no idea how to deal with children. From 16 year olds beating up pre-teens like us, to just falling asleep watching netflix during curfew. 9/

Lets talk about the volounteers who were looking after the kids: At the time I was in 5th grade (10-11yo) and many of the volounteers were only a few years older (14-16yo). At the time it made sense because puberty already hit, they were taller and had deeper voice 8/

Besides, instead of motivating kids to take part in activities like this was never that they may win a prize, whether thats extra freetime or chocolate. We never had prizes. All of these were mandatory. 7/

Despite this, the teachers decided it would be a fun activity to make kids take off their shoes, throw it in the sand and have you and another 10 kids jump on it as a "fun race". Mind you, shoes were extremely expensive and many families couldnt just afford new ones out of blue6/

This was in 2012 when the country was recovering from the economic crisis both from 2008 and from the system change (east europe). Everyone's financial status was rather poor and a lot of people struggled to put food on the table at the end of the month 5/

The building had two wings, for boys and girls. You were prohibited to enter the other genders wing under ANY circumstances. A friend of mine had her little brother stay in the camp too and they never let her take stuff to him. He had to go to the main area to pick it up 4/

Also the gender separation was so fucking real. They forced us to play soccer as boys vs girl so they can watch. There was literally only one girl who wanted to play, the rest of us were standing on the soccer field doing nothing. Boys scored like 999-0 (much surprise) 3/

She noticed the chords and instructed me to play them. I told them I dont know them and I had no access to internet to look it up. She made me sit in front of a bunch of kids with a guitar in my hand doing nothing, because I couldnt play the chords. 2/

So you know how some hymn-books have chords in them so you can follow it up with instrumental? I was 9 years old and I brought my guitar to the camp to sing songs with my friends, but the camp leader knew this. 1/
